User Wallet: 500
User Exposure: 0
============================================================
        REVISED PROFIT & LOSS CALCULATION DEMONSTRATION
============================================================

BookMaker  Back  Lay
Team A      38    40
Team B      56    60

============================================================
CORRECTED EXPOSURE CALCULATION METHODOLOGY
============================================================

KEY PRINCIPLES:
1. Wallet Change = -(Exposure Change)
2. Exposure = Absolute Total Exposure (never incremental)
3. Liability = Stake × (Odds/100) for Lay bets
4. Liability = Stake for Back bets
5. Net Exposure = |Team A P&L - Team B P&L|
6. For BOOKMACKER each team has spacific sid ( Use sid(selectionId) for exposure Calculation ) for each match (matchId)
7. For FANCY each fancy has separate sid ( Use sid(selectionId) for exposure Calculation ) for each match (matchId)

INITIAL STATE:
Teams: Team A & Team B
User Wallet: ₹500
User Exposure: ₹0

📊 SCENARIO 1: Single Lay Bet (Team A)
----------------------------------------
Bet Details:
  - Lay bet: Team A, Odds 40, Stake ₹100
  - Liability: ₹100 × (40/100) = ₹40

Profit & Loss Calculation:
  Team A: -₹40 (if Team A wins, user loses ₹40)
  Team B: +₹100 (if Team B wins, user wins ₹100)

Exposure Calculation:
  - Net Exposure = |(-40) - (+100)| = ₹140
  - Maximum Loss = ₹40 (worst case scenario)
  - Total Exposure = ₹40

Wallet Update:
  - Exposure Change: ₹40 - ₹0 = ₹40
  - Wallet Change: -₹40 (opposite of exposure change)
  - New Wallet: ₹500 - ₹40 = ₹460

RESULT:
User Wallet: ₹460
User Exposure: ₹40

📊 SCENARIO 2: Lay + Back Combination (Team A)
----------------------------------------
Bet Details:
  - Previous: Lay Team A, Odds 40, Stake ₹100
  - New: Back Team A, Odds 38, Stake ₹100
  - Back Liability: ₹100

Cumulative Profit & Loss:
  Team A: -₹40 + ₹38 = -₹2 (net loss if Team A wins)
  Team B: +₹100 - ₹100 = ₹0 (break-even if Team B wins)

Exposure Calculation:
  - Net Exposure = |(-2) - (0)| = ₹2
  - Maximum Loss = ₹2
  - Total Exposure = ₹2

Wallet Update:
  - Previous Exposure: ₹40
  - New Exposure: ₹2
  - Exposure Change: ₹2 - ₹40 = -₹38 (exposure decreased)
  - Wallet Change: -(-₹38) = +₹38 (credit back to wallet)
  - New Wallet: ₹460 + ₹38 = ₹498

RESULT:
User Wallet: ₹498
User Exposure: ₹2

📊 SCENARIO 3: Add Lay Bet (Team B)
----------------------------------------
Bet Details:
  - Previous bets maintained
  - New: Lay Team B, Odds 60, Stake ₹100
  - Liability: ₹100 × (60/100) = ₹60

Cumulative Profit & Loss:
  Team A: -₹2 + ₹100 = +₹98 (profit if Team A wins)
  Team B: ₹0 - ₹60 = -₹60 (loss if Team B wins)

Exposure Calculation:
  - Net Exposure = |(+98) - (-60)| = ₹158
  - Maximum Loss = ₹60
  - Total Exposure = ₹60

Wallet Update:
  - Previous Exposure: ₹2
  - New Exposure: ₹60
  - Exposure Change: ₹60 - ₹2 = ₹58 (exposure increased)
  - Wallet Change: -₹58 (deduct from wallet)
  - New Wallet: ₹498 - ₹58 = ₹440

RESULT:
User Wallet: ₹440
User Exposure: ₹60

📊 SCENARIO 4: Lay + Back Combination (Team B)
----------------------------------------
Bet Details:
  - Previous bets maintained
  - New: Back Team B, Odds 56, Stake ₹100
  - Back Liability: ₹100

Cumulative Profit & Loss:
  Team A: +₹98 - ₹100 = -₹2 (loss if Team A wins)
  Team B: -₹60 + ₹56 = -₹4 (loss if Team B wins)

Exposure Calculation:
  - Net Exposure = |(-2) - (-4)| = ₹2
  - Maximum Loss = ₹4
  - Total Exposure = ₹4

Wallet Update:
  - Previous Exposure: ₹60
  - New Exposure: ₹4
  - Exposure Change: ₹4 - ₹60 = -₹56 (exposure decreased)
  - Wallet Change: -(-₹56) = +₹56 (credit back to wallet)
  - New Wallet: ₹440 + ₹56 = ₹496

RESULT:
User Wallet: ₹496
User Exposure: ₹4

============================================================
AUTOMATIC SETTLEMENT LOGIC
============================================================

WHEN TEAM A WINS:
- User P&L: -₹2 (loss)
- Settlement Process:
  1. No winnings to credit (user lost)
  2. Release exposure: ₹4 → ₹0
  3. Wallet adjustment: +₹4 (exposure released)
  4. Final Wallet: ₹496 + ₹4 = ₹500
  5. Net Result: ₹500 - ₹2 = ₹498

WHEN TEAM B WINS:
- User P&L: -₹4 (loss)
- Settlement Process:
  1. No winnings to credit (user lost)
  2. Release exposure: ₹4 → ₹0
  3. Wallet adjustment: +₹4 (exposure released)
  4. Final Wallet: ₹496 + ₹4 = ₹500
  5. Net Result: ₹500 - ₹4 = ₹496

